cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on accelerating and compressing Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for Computer Vision tasks, which is a core area of research in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a compression and acceleration pipeline that involves sparsification, quantization, and entropy encoding, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning research. Therefore, the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on image datasets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
